docs.snippet: More than a week after President Obama signed the sweeping new health care law, many of us are still scratching our heads. What just happened?

docs.lead_paragraph: The new health care law is expected to extend coverage to as many as 32 million uninsured Americans over the next decade. Under the law, most Americans will be required to have health insurance by 2014 and the most affluent households will face higher taxes. Here, how the overhaul could affect those who have health insurance now and those who do not. If you're sick, you could get coverage three months from now.
